HEADWORD: Discoverture
<hw>Dis*cov"er*ture</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>dis-</ets> + <ets>coverture</ets>: cf. OF. <ets>descoverture</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Discovery.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A state of being released from coverture; freedom of a woman from the coverture of a husband.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Discovery</ent>⟦br⟧
